const n="# React Best Practices\n\n<p style=\"width: 100%; text-align: right; padding-right: 20px\"><em>8 November 2025</em></p>\n\n## Component Organization\n\n### Functional Components\n\nAlways use functional components with hooks:\n\n```jsx\nimport { useState } from 'react'\n\nexport default function Counter() {\n  const [count, setCount] = useState(0)\n\n  return (\n    <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>\n      Count: {count}\n    </button>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n## Hooks\n\n### useState\n\nManaging local component state:\n\n```jsx\nconst [value, setValue] = useState('')\n```\n\n### useEffect\n\nRunning side effects:\n\n```jsx\nuseEffect(() => {\n  // Effect code here\n  return () => {\n    // Cleanup code here\n  }\n}, [dependencies])\n```\n\n## Performance Tips\n\n1. **Memoization** - Use `React.memo` for expensive components\n2. **Code Splitting** - Lazy load routes and components\n3. **Key Props** - Always provide keys in lists\n4. **Avoid Inline Objects** - Define objects outside render\n\n## Styling\n\n### CSS Modules\n\n```jsx\nimport styles from './Component.module.css'\n\nexport default function Component() {\n  return <div className={styles.container}></div>\n}\n```\n\n### Tailwind CSS\n\n```jsx\nexport default function Component() {\n  return <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center\"></div>\n}\n```\n\n## Testing\n\n```jsx\nimport { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport Component from './Component'\n\ntest('renders component', () => {\n  render(<Component />)\n  expect(screen.getByText('Hello')).toBeInTheDocument()\n})\n```\n\nKeep these practices in mind for better, more maintainable React code! ðŸš€\n\n";export{n as default};
